<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Missing-Path on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/missing-path/</link><description>Recent content in Missing-Path on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/missing-path/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash No Such File or Directory Error</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/no-such-file/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/no-such-file/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-no-such-file-or-directory-error-fix"&gt;Bash No Such File or Directory Error Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when Bash tries to access a file, directory, or executable that doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist at the specified path.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bash resolves every path reference — whether for executing a command, sourcing a file, or reading input. If the path is wrong, the file was moved, or the name is misspelled, this error is raised.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Misspelled filename or path&lt;/strong&gt; — a typo in the file or directory name.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;File was deleted or moved&lt;/strong&gt; — referencing a path that no longer exists.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Relative path used incorrectly&lt;/strong&gt; — the working directory isn&amp;rsquo;t what you expect.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing shebang target&lt;/strong&gt; — script has &lt;code&gt;#!/usr/bin/env notreal&lt;/code&gt; with no such interpreter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-verify-the-path-exists"&gt;Fix 1: Verify the path exists&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls -la /path/to/file
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Or check before using&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;[[&lt;/span&gt; -f &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$FILE&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;]]&lt;/span&gt;; &lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;then&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; source &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$FILE&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;else&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;File not found: &lt;/span&gt;$FILE&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;fi&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-use-absolute-paths-for-reliability"&gt;Fix 2: Use absolute paths for reliability&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Instead of&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source config.sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Use&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;source /home/user/project/config.sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-check-for-typos-and-whitespace"&gt;Fix 3: Check for typos and whitespace&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Trailing whitespace causes invisible errors&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;file&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;config.sh &amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Note the trailing space&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;$file&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# No such file or directory&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-4-use-which-or-command--v-to-locate-executables"&gt;Fix 4: Use &lt;code&gt;which&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;command -v&lt;/code&gt; to locate executables&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;which mycommand &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Command not found&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;command -v mycommand &lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Command not found&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="examples"&gt;Examples&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ source missing-file.sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bash: missing-file.sh: No such file or directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ ./deploy.sh
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;bash: ./deploy.sh: No such file or directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;$ ls /tmp/data
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;ls: cannot access &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#39;/tmp/data&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;: No such file or directory
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h2 id="related-errors"&gt;Related Errors&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="is-a-directory"&gt;Is a Directory&lt;/a&gt; — trying to use a directory where a file is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="not-a-directory"&gt;Not a Directory&lt;/a&gt; — trying to use a file where a directory is expected.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href="command-not-found"&gt;Command Not Found&lt;/a&gt; — command doesn&amp;rsquo;t exist in PATH.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>